ctoria</a>, which is also bordered by Kenya and Tanzania.</p>\n<p>Uganda takes its name from the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buganda\" title=\"Buganda\">Buganda</a> kingdom, which encompassed a portion of the south of the country including the capital <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kampala\" title=\"Kampala\">Kampala</a>. Half of the population of the country lives below the international poverty line of US$1.25 a day.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uganda#cite_note-4\"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup></p>\n<table id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\">\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div id=\"toctitle\"'),(2,243,'Zaire',NULL,'upload/Zaire.txt',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-25 09:09:01','	<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\">Zaire</h1>\n		<div id=\"bodyContent\">\n			<h3 id=\"siteSub\"></h3>\n			<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n									<div id=\"jump-to-nav\">Jump to: <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zaire#column-one\">navigation</a>, <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zaire#searchInput\">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->\n			<div class=\"dablink\">For other uses, see <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zaire_(disambiguation)\" title=\"Zaire (disambiguation)\">Zaire (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks ambox ambox-content\" style=\"\">\n<tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\">\n<div style=\"width: 52px;\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Question_book-new.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Question book-new.svg\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"39\" /></a></div>\n</td>\n<td class=\"mbox-text\" style=\"\">This article <b>needs additional <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources#Inline_citations\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citing sources\">citations</a> for <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiabil