a></td>\n<td>10.13/km<sup>2</sup>&#160;<br />\n26.2/sq&#160;mi</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Currency\" title=\"Currency\">Currency</a></th>\n<td><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saint_Helena_pound\" title=\"Saint Helena pound\">Saint Helena pound</a> (<code><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217\" title=\"ISO 4217\">SHP</a></code>)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time_zone\" title=\"Time zone\">Time zone</a></th>\n<td>GMT <span style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">(<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coordinated_Universal_Time\" title=\"Coordinated Universal Time\">UTC</a>+0)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Country_code_top-level_domain\" title=\"Country code top-level domain\">Internet TLD</a></th>\n<td><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/.sh\" title=\".sh\">.sh</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_country_calling_codes\" title=\"List of country calling codes\">Calling code</a></th>\n<td>290</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p><b>Saint Helena</b> (pronounced <span title=\"Pronunciation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\">/Àåse…™nt h…ôÀàliÀên…ô/</a></span> <i>saint h…ô-<span style=\"font-variant:small-caps;\">lee</span>-n…ô</i>), named after <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helena_of_Constantinople\" title=\"Helena of Constantinople\" class=\"mw-redirect\">St&#160;Helena of Constantinople</a>, is an island of <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volcano\" title=\"Volcano\">volcanic</a> origin in the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Atlantic_Ocean\" title=\"South Atlantic Ocean\" class=\"mw-redirect\">South Atlantic Ocean</a>. It is part of the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_overseas_territory\" title=\"British overseas territory\" class=\"mw-redirect\">British overseas territory</a> of <b><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saint_Helena,_Ascension_and_Tristan_da_Cunha\" title=\"Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha\">Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha</a></b> <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/St._Helena#cite_note-1\"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> which also includes <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ascension_Island\" title=\"Ascension Island\">Ascension Island</a> and the islands of <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tristan_da_Cunha\" title=\"Tristan da Cunha\">Tristan da Cunha</a>.</p>\n<p>The island has a history of over 500 years since it was first discovered as an uninhabited island by the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Portugal\" title=\"Portugal\">Portuguese</a> in 1502. Britain\'s second oldest remaining colony (after <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bermuda\" title=\"Bermuda\">Bermuda</a>), Saint Helena is one of the most isolated islands in the world and was for several centuries of vital strategic importance to ships sailing to Europe from Asia and South Africa. For several centuries, the British used the island as a place of exile, most notably for <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Napoleon_I_of_France\" title=\"Napoleon I of France\">Napoleon Bonaparte</a>, <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dinuzulu_kaCetshwayo\" title=\"Dinuzulu kaCetshwayo\">Dinuzulu kaCetshwayo</a> and over 5,000 <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boer\" title=\"Boer\">Boer</a> prisoners.</p>\n<table id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\">\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div id=\"toctitle\"'),(16,261,'Madagascar',NULL,'upload/Madagascar.txt',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-20 08:33:43','	<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\">Madagascar</h1>\n		<div id=\"bodyContent\">\n			<h3 id=\"siteSub\"></h3>\n			<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n									<div id=\"jump-to-nav\">J