ass=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angola#cite_note-imf2-1\"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup>&#160;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\"><b><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_Development_Index\" title=\"Human Development Index\">HDI</a></b>&#160;(2007)</td>\n<td><span style=\"color: #0c0; font-size: larger;\">‚ñ≤</span>0.564&#160;(<font color=\"#FFCC00\">medium</font>)&#160;(<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_countries_by_Human_Development_Index\" title=\"List of countries by Human Development Index\">143rd</a>)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align:middle;\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Currency\" title=\"Currency\">Currency</a></th>\n<td><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angolan_kwanza\" title=\"Angolan kwanza\">Kwanza</a> (<code><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217\" title=\"ISO 4217\">AOA</a></code>)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"mergedtoprow\">\n<th colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time_zone\" title=\"Time zone\">Time zone</a></th>\n<td><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Africa_Time\" title=\"West Africa Time\">WAT</a> <span style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">(<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coordinated_Universal_Time\" title=\"Coordinated Universal Time\">UTC</a>+1)</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"mergedbottomrow\">\n<td style=\"width:1em; padding:0 0 0 0.6em;\">&#160;-&#160;</td>\n<td style=\"padding-left:0em;\">Summer&#160;(<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daylight_saving_time\" title=\"Daylight saving time\">DST</a>)</td>\n<td><i>not observed</i>&#160;(<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coordinated_Universal_Time\" title=\"Coordinated Universal Time\">UTC</a>+1)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Right-_and_left-hand_traffic\" title=\"Right- and left-hand traffic\">Drives on the</a></th>\n<td>right</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Country_code_top-level_domain\" title=\"Country code top-level domain\">Internet TLD</a></th>\n<td><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/.ao\" title=\".ao\">.ao</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_country_calling_codes\" title=\"List of country calling codes\">Calling code</a></th>\n<td>244</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p><b>Angola</b>, officially the <b>Republic of Angola</b> (<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Portuguese_language\" title=\"Portuguese language\">Portuguese</a>: <span lang=\"pt\" xml:lang=\"pt\"><i>Rep√∫blica de Angola</i></span>, <small>pronounced&#160;</small><span title=\"Pronunciation in IPA\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_Portuguese\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for Portuguese\">[ Å…õÀàpublik…ê d…® …êÃÉÀà…°…îl…ê]</a></span>; <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kongo_language\" title=\"Kongo language\">Kongo</a>: <span lang=\"kg\" xml:lang=\"kg\">Repubilika ya Ngola</span>), is a country in south-central <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Africa\" title=\"Africa\">Africa</a> bordered by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Namibia\" title=\"Namibia\">Namibia</a> on the south, <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo\" title=\"Democratic Republic of the Congo\">Democratic Republic of the Congo</a> on the north, and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zambia\" title=\"Zambia\">Zambia</a> on the east; its west coast is on the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atlantic_Ocean\" title=\"Atlantic Ocean\">Atlantic Ocean</a>. The <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enclave_and_exclave\" title=\"Enclave and exclave\">exclave</a> province of <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cabinda_(province)\" title=\"Cabinda (province)\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Cabinda</a> has a border with the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republic_of_the_Congo\" title=\"Republic of the Congo\">Republic of the Congo</a> and the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo\" title=\"Democratic Republic of the Congo\">Democratic Republic of the Congo</a>. Angola was a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Portuguese_West_Africa\" title=\"Portuguese West Africa\">Portuguese overseas territory</a> from the 16th century to <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1975\" title=\"1975\">1975</a>. After independence, Angola was the scene of an intense <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angolan_Civil_War\" title=\"Angolan Civil War\">civil war from 1975 to 2002</a>. The country is the second-largest <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petroleum\" title=\"Petroleum\">petroleum</a> and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diamond\" title=\"Diamond\">diamond</a> producer in <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sub-Saharan\" title=\"Sub-Saharan\" class=\"mw-redirect\">sub-Saharan</a> Africa; however, its <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Life_expectancy\" title=\"Life expectancy\">life expectancy</a> and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infant_mortality\" title=\"Infant mortality\">infant mortality</a> rates are both among the worst ranked in the world. In August 2006, a peace treaty was signed with a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Faction\" title=\"Faction\">faction</a> of the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Front_for_the_Liberation_of_the_Enclave_of_Cabinda\" title=\"Front for the Liberation of the Enclave of Cabinda\">FLEC</a>, a separatist guerrilla group from the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cabinda_Province\" title=\"Cabinda Province\">Cabinda</a> exclave in the North, which is still active.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angola#cite_note-2\"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> About 65% of Angola\'s oil comes from that region.</p>\n<table id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\">\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div id=\"toctitle\"'),(18,252,'Somalia',NULL,'upload/Somalia.txt',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-25 13:40:43','	<