itle=\"Bantu languages\">Bantu</a> speaking people), based on <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethnolinguistic\" title=\"Ethnolinguistic\" class=\"mw-redirect\">ethnolinguistic</a> affiliation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nilotic#cite_note-3\"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup> Etymologically, the terms Nilotic and Nilote (also spelled Nilot) derive from the Nile Valley, specifically the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Upper_Nile,_Sudan\" title=\"Upper Nile, Sudan\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Upper Nile</a> and its tributaries, where most Sudanese Nilo-Saharan-speaking people live.</p>\n<table id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\">\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div id=\"toctitle\"'),(155,NULL,'Nubian_Pharaohs',NULL,'upload/Nubian_Pharaohs.txt',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-24 10:22:33',''),(156,NULL,'Nubian_Pharaohs',NULL,'upload/Nubian_Pharaohs.txt',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-24 10:22:33',''),(157,NULL,'Kushite_Empire',NULL,'upload/Kushite_Empire.txt',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-24 10:46:34','	<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\">Twenty-fifth dynasty of Egypt</h1>\n		<div id=\"bodyContent\">\n			<h3 id=\"siteSub\"></h3>\n			<div id=\"contentSub\">¬†¬†(Redirected from <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Kushite_Empire&amp;redirect=no\" title=\"Kushite Empire\">Kushite Empire</a>)</div>\n									<div id=\"jump-to-nav\">Jump to: <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kushite_Empire#column-one\">navigation</a>, <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kushite_Empire#searchInput\">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->\n			<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Kushite_empire_700bc.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/8/84/Kushite_empire_700bc.jpg/250px-Kushite_empire_700bc.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"243\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>\n<div class=\"thumbcaption\">\n<div class=\