ational Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\">/</a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"secondary stress\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">Àå</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'s\' in \'sigh\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">s</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'ou\' in \'pout\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">a ä</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'th\' in \'thigh\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">Œ∏</span></a></span> <span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'s\' in \'sigh\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">s</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"long \'oo\' in \'food\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">uÀê</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"primary stress\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">Àà</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'d\' in \'dye\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">d</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"short \'a\' in \'bad\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">√¶</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'n\' in \'nigh\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">n</span></a></span><span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\">/</a></span></span> or <span style=\"white-space:nowrap;\"><span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\">/</a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'s\' in \'sigh\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">s</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"long \'oo\' in \'food\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">uÀê</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"primary stress\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">Àà</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'d\' in \'dye\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">d</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'a\' in \'father\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">…ëÀê</span></a></span><span class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English#Key\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\"><span title=\"\'n\' in \'nigh\'\" style=\"border-bottom:1px dotted\">n</span></a></span><span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English\" title=\"Wikipedia:IPA for English\">/</a></span></span>), officially the <b>Republic of South Sudan</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-factbook_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Sudan#cite_note-factbook-7\"><span>[</span>8<span>]</span></a></sup> is a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Landlocked_country\" title=\"Landlocked country\">landlocked country</a> located between <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_Africa\" title=\"Central Africa\">Central Africa</a> and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Africa\" title=\"Eastern Africa\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Eastern Africa</a>. Its current capital is <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Juba\" title=\"Juba\">Juba</a>, which is also its largest city; the capital city is planned to be moved to the more centrally-located <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ramciel\" title=\"Ramciel\">Ramciel</a> in the future.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BBCprofile_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Sudan#cite_note-BBCprofile-8\"><span>[</span>9<span>]</span></a></sup> South Sudan is bordered by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethiopia\" title=\"Ethiopia\">Ethiopia</a> to the east, <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kenya\" title=\"Kenya\">Kenya</a> to the southeast, <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uganda\" title=\"Uganda\">Uganda</a> to the south, the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo\" title=\"Democratic Republic of the Congo\">Democratic Republic of the Congo</a> to the southwest, the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Central_African_Republic\" title=\"Central African Republic\">Central African Republic</a> to the west, and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudan\" title=\"Sudan\">Sudan</a> to the north. South Sudan includes the vast <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swamp\" title=\"Swamp\">swamp</a> region of the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudd\" title=\"Sudd\">Sudd</a> formed by the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/White_Nile\" title=\"White Nile\">White Nile</a>, locally called the <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/White_Nile\" title=\"White Nile\">Bahr al Jabal</a></i>.</p>\n<p>What are now the modern states of South Sudan and Sudan were part of <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Egypt\" title=\"Egypt\">Egypt</a> under the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Dynasty\" title=\"Muhammad Ali Dynasty\">Muhammad Ali Dynasty</a>, later being governed as an <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anglo-Egyptian_Sudan\" title=\"Anglo-Egyptian Sudan\">Anglo-Egyptian condominium</a> until Sudanese independence was achieved in 1956. Following the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/First_Sudanese_Civil_War\" title=\"First Sudanese Civil War\">First Sudanese Civil War</a>, the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southern_Sudan_Autonomous_Region\" title=\"Southern Sudan Autonomous Region\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Southern Sudan Autonomous Region</a> was formed in 1972 and lasted until 1983. A <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Sudanese_civil_war\" title=\"Second Sudanese civil war\" class=\"mw-redirect\">second Sudanese civil war</a> soon developed and ended with the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comprehensive_Peace_Agreement\" title=\"Comprehensive Peace Agreement\">Comprehensive Peace Agreement</a> of 2005. Later that year, southern autonomy was restored when an <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autonomous_Government_of_Southern_Sudan\" title=\"Autonomous Government of Southern Sudan\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Autonomous Government of Southern Sudan</a> was formed. South Sudan became an independent state on 9 July 2011.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Sudan#cite_note-9\"><span>[</span>10<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Sudan#cite_note-10\"><span>[</span>11<span>]</span></a></sup> On 14 July 2011, South Sudan became a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Nations_member_state\" title=\"United Nations member state\" class=\"mw-redirect\">United Nations member state</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Sudan#cite_note-11\"><span>[</span>12<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Sudan#cite_note-12\"><span>[</span>13<span>]</span></a></sup> It joined the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/African_Union\" title=\"African Union\">African Union</a> on 28 July 2011.<sup id=\"cite_ref-au54_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Sudan#cite_note-au54-13\"><span>[</span>14<span>]</span></a></sup></p>\n<p>South Sudan is one of the poorest countries with possibly the worst health situation in the world.<sup id=\"cite_ref-health_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Sudan#cite_note-health-14\"><span>[</span>15<span>]</span></a></sup></p>\n<table id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\">\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div id=\"toctitle\"'),(217,NULL,'http://travel.state.gov/visa/i',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2012-10-05 23:31:15',NULL),(218,NULL,'Diversity_Visa',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2012-10-05 23:32:17',NULL),(219,NULL,'Lake_Victoria',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2013-03-08 07:13:20',NULL),(220,NULL,'Equatorial_Guinea',NULL,'upload/Equatorial_Guinea.txt',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2013-10-28 02:06:19','	<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang